<TITLE> Cross-country runner 'against drugs' nears finish line </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 5 (bdnews24.com)Young Ruhul Islam who set off on a cross-country marathon to raise awareness about drugs will reach the end of his near month-long run on Wednesday. Twenty-eight year old Ruhul began his marathon sprint on Jan 13 from Teknaf, the southernmost tip of Bangladesh, and will end it at Zero Point, the northwest boundary of Bangladesh in Tentulia near the India border. Ruhul, who has so far run about 1,000 kilometres to create awareness among the publicand young people in particularabout the dangers of drug taking, reached Panchagarh Tuesday. His cross-country run has taken him through 13 districts, during which he visited educational institutions, youth organisations and press clubs, sharing views with ordinary people throughout his journey. His aim was to initiate "a social movement against drugs". Ruhul of Muthurapur village, Thakurgaon, ran 35 kilometres a day on average and has spent about Tk 17,000 for the cause. bdnews2
